{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SYMFDq8uCuFv3nCpZia2bJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n     2→\n     3→### Session 12 — state corruption fix #4 (2026-03-27T14:24Z)\n     4→\n     5→- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` despite committed `done` state and proof docs in git.\n     6→- Epic-16 at `backlog` in sprint-status.yaml despite `done` in sprint-state.json epics section (inconsistent within same file).\n     7→- Sprint.done=70 despite epics.epic-16.storiesDone=8 — internal sprint-state.json inconsistency.\n     8→- This is the 4th time today. Root cause: ralph state reconciliation overwrites story statuses without checking git history or proof documents.\n     9→- **CRITICAL BUG**: The reconciliation code does not verify whether proof documents exist before resetting story status. This wastes entire sessions on no-op state fixes.\n    10→\n    11→## Token Report\n    12→- Total tool calls: ~12\n    13→- By tool: Read: 4, Edit: 6, Bash: 2\n    14→- Files read: 3 unique, 4 total reads\n    15→- Redundant operations: This entire session is redundant — same fix applied 4 times today\n    16→\n    17→### Session 11 — state corruption fix (2026-03-27T14:19Z)\n    18→\n    19→- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` in sprint-state.json despite being committed as `done` in git.\n    20→- Epic 16 AGAIN at `backlog` in sprint-status.yaml despite being complete.\n    21→- This is the THIRD time this session — ralph state reconciliation keeps overwriting committed state.\n    22→- Root cause needs permanent fix: ralph's state reconciliation must check git log for committed proof documents before resetting status.\n    23→- No stories to execute — all sprint work is complete.\n    24→\n    25→## Token Report\n    26→- Total tool calls: ~15\n    27→- By tool: Read: 6, Bash: 3, Edit: 4, Grep: 2\n    28→- Files read: 4 unique, 6 total reads\n    29→- Redundant operations: This entire session is redundant — same fix applied 3 times today\n    30→\n    31→### Session 10 — state corruption fix (2026-03-27T14:15Z)\n    32→\n    33→- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 were at `review` in sprint-state.json despite being committed as `done` with proof documents in git (commits 09ae9a0, 4d6af09, f597711, 5b7fa94).\n    34→- Epic 16 was at `backlog` in sprint-status.yaml despite commit cb82adb marking it complete.\n    35→- Root cause: ralph state reconciliation overwrites committed state. This is a recurring issue (also seen in session 9).\n    36→- Fixed manually by updating sprint-state.json and sprint-status.yaml to match git truth.\n    37→- No stories executed this session — all work was already done.\n    38→\n    39→## Token Report\n    40→- Total tool calls: ~12\n    41→- By tool: Read: 3, Bash: 5, Edit: 1, Glob: 1, Write: 1\n    42→- Files read: 4 unique, 5 total reads\n    43→- Redundant operations: None\n    44→\n    45→### State corruption fix (2026-03-27T13:48Z)\n    46→\n    47→Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7 were at `review` in sprint-state.json despite committed as done with proof documents. Fixed by restoring `done` status. Same root cause as previous session — ralph state reconciliation overwriting committed state.\n    48→\n    49→### 16-8-update-all-tests — create-story (2026-03-27T13:49Z)\n    50→\n    51→- Ambiguity in epic definition: Task 8 in tech-spec is terse (\"Update all tests\") with no specific ACs. Derived ACs from tech-spec testing strategy.\n    52→- Used legacy tag names (`cli-verifiable`) per instruction — `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` maps them to `test-provable` at parse time.\n    53→- Risk: Story may require zero code changes if previous stories already added all tests.\n    54→\n    55→## Token Report\n    56→- Total tool calls: 17\n    57→- By tool: Read: 7, Grep: 7, Glob: 3, Write: 1\n    58→- Files read: 9 unique, 10 total reads\n    59→- Redundant operations: None\n    60→\n    61→### 16-8-update-all-tests — dev (2026-03-27T13:56Z)\n    62→\n    63→- Pre-existing BATS failures: 6 BATS integration tests fail (ralph loop tests, unrelated to verification tier rework).\n    64→- Zero code changes needed — audit confirmed complete coverage from stories 16-1 through 16-7.\n    65→\n    66→## Token Report\n    67→- Total tool calls: 16\n    68→- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 9, Write: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n    69→- Files read: 9 unique, 9 total reads\n    70→- Redundant operations: None\n    71→\n    72→### 16-8-update-all-tests — code-review (2026-03-27T14:00Z)\n    73→\n    74→- LOW-1: `classifyTier` barrel re-export not tested through index.ts\n    75→- LOW-2: Line number references in Dev Agent Record will drift\n    76→- LOW-3: No explicit test for runtime > test priority in classifyTier\n    77→\n    78→## Token Report\n    79→- Total tool calls: 15\n    80→- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 9, Edit: 2, Grep: 3, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n    81→- Files read: 12 unique, 12 total reads\n    82→- Redundant operations: None\n    83→\n    84→### 16-8-update-all-tests — verify (2026-03-27T14:05Z)\n    85→\n    86→ALL_PASS (12/12 ACs). Test-provable tier — no Docker needed. Build, 4015 tests, coverage 96.86%.\n    87→\n    88→## Token Report\n    89→- Total tool calls: 17\n    90→- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 3, Grep: 8, Write: 2\n    91→- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n    92→- Redundant operations: Proof written twice (format fix). Separate vitest runs for pass count vs coverage.\n    93→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01WKb4pPG6PLuxxxnWVqC91B","session_id":"4e7b67ce-a5dd-4961-be94-794643eae587","uuid":"cfdaa9c3-2402-4d81-811a-1f2002a1a079","timestamp":"2026-03-27T14:26:03.690Z"}
