{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01At9svx3fyYDgA72zbZYKef","type":"tool_result","content":"  1600→| create-story | 344 | $36.58 | 5.8% |\n  1601→| code-review | 305 | $34.70 | 5.5% |\n  1602→| dev-story | 271 | $30.07 | 4.8% |\n  1603→\n  1604→### Tool breakdown\n  1605→\n  1606→| Tool | Calls | Cost | % |\n  1607→|------|-------|------|---|\n  1608→| Bash | 2,011 | $247.23 | 39.4% |\n  1609→| Read | 899 | $118.32 | 18.8% |\n  1610→| Edit | 589 | $74.99 | 11.9% |\n  1611→| Agent | 414 | $54.54 | 8.7% |\n  1612→\n  1613→### Waste analysis\n  1614→\n  1615→- **Sessions 9-11 combined:** ~$36 estimated spend on state corruption fixes (3 sessions x ~$12 each). Zero productive output.\n  1616→- **\"unknown\" story bucket:** $116.32 (18.5%) remains unattributed — likely orchestrator overhead, retros, and state fixes that don't tag a story ID.\n  1617→- **Verification phase dominance:** 56.2% of total spend. This is structurally expected (verification runs builds, tests, coverage) but the absolute number ($352.82) suggests optimization opportunities — e.g., caching test results across verify retries.\n  1618→\n  1619→## 4. What Went Well\n  1620→\n  1621→- **Sprint is 100% complete.** All 16 epics, all 74 stories — done. This is a major milestone.\n  1622→- **State fix was fast.** Despite being the third time, the fix took ~5 minutes with ~15 tool calls.\n  1623→- **Issues log captured the pattern clearly.** The subagent correctly identified the fix as redundant and documented it, making this retro straightforward.\n  1624→- **Total project cost is reasonable.** $627.68 for 74 stories across 16 epics = $8.48/epic average, $3.36/story average. For an autonomous sprint with full dev-review-verify cycles, this is efficient.\n  1625→\n  1626→## 5. What Went Wrong\n  1627→\n  1628→- **State reconciliation bug persists after six sessions.** First flagged in session 5, still unfixed in session 11. This is now the single highest-impact bug in the system.\n  1629→- **Ralph keeps spawning sessions when sprint is done.** Sessions 9, 10, and 11 had no productive work. Ralph should detect sprint completion and stop.\n  1630→- **$36+ burned on identical state fixes.** Three sessions doing the exact same manual edit to `sprint-state.json`. This is the definition of waste.\n  1631→- **No automated guard against state regression.** There is no pre-commit hook or reconciliation check that prevents `done` -> `review` transitions.\n  1632→\n  1633→## 6. Lessons Learned\n  1634→\n  1635→1. **`done` must be a terminal state.** No reconciliation logic should ever regress a story from `done` to any earlier state. This needs to be enforced at the write level, not caught after the fact.\n  1636→\n  1637→2. **Sprint completion should halt ralph.** When `sprint.done === sprint.total`, ralph should exit cleanly. Spawning new sessions that discover nothing to do creates a loop of overhead (retro, state repair, more retro).\n  1638→\n  1639→3. **State fixes should be idempotent and persistent.** If the same fix is applied three times in one day and keeps getting reverted, the fix is happening at the wrong layer. The reconciliation logic itself must be patched, not the data it corrupts.\n  1640→\n  1641→4. **Retro sessions compound the cost.** Each state-fix session spawns a retro, which costs ~$12. Three unnecessary retros = ~$36. The retro phase is 9.7% of total spend — if half of those retros were for zero-work sessions, that is ~$30 wasted on retrospecting nothing.\n  1642→\n  1643→5. **Story 16-8 was effectively a no-op.** The dev phase confirmed zero code changes were needed. Stories that audit existing state and find nothing wrong should have a fast-exit path rather than going through full dev-review-verify cycles.\n  1644→\n  1645→## 7. Action Items\n  1646→\n  1647→| # | Action | Priority | Owner | Status |\n  1648→|---|--------|----------|-------|--------|\n  1649→| 1 | **Fix state reconciliation to treat `done` as terminal/immutable** — never regress from `done` to any earlier status. Check git log for committed proof documents before resetting. | CRITICAL | Infrastructure | OPEN (flagged sessions 5-11, SEVEN consecutive) |\n  1650→| 2 | **Add ralph session termination when sprint is 100% complete** — exit cleanly when `sprint.done === sprint.total` | HIGH | Infrastructure | OPEN (flagged sessions 9-11) |\n  1651→| 3 | **Recompute `sprint.done` and per-epic counters from actual story statuses** — derived values should never diverge from source data | HIGH | Infrastructure | OPEN (flagged session 9) |\n  1652→| 4 | **Add fast-exit path for audit/no-op stories** — skip full dev-review-verify when dev phase produces zero changes | MEDIUM | Process | NEW |\n  1653→| 5 | **Fix 6 pre-existing BATS test failures** | MEDIUM | Tech debt | OPEN (carried forward) |\n  1654→| 6 | **Provide proof document format template to verify subagents** — eliminate recurring \"write proof twice\" pattern | MEDIUM | Process | OPEN (carried forward) |\n  1655→| 7 | **Reduce \"unknown\" story cost bucket** (18.5% / $116.32 unattributed spend) | LOW | Tooling | OPEN (carried forward) |\n  1656→| 8 | **Plan next sprint** — all 16 epics complete, project at natural milestone | HIGH | PM | OPEN (carried forward) |\n  1657→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01WKb4pPG6PLuxxxnWVqC91B","session_id":"4e7b67ce-a5dd-4961-be94-794643eae587","uuid":"7a78f37e-5b8d-49f6-a858-6d5e24e0145e","timestamp":"2026-03-27T14:26:31.894Z"}
