 went well** — stories completed, bugs fixed, process improvements\n5. **What went wrong** — failures, blockers, stuck stories, wasted iterations\n6. **Lessons learned** — patterns to repeat or avoid\n7. **Action items** — concrete next steps\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-27.md.\n\nSince a session retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously.\nDo NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","agentId":"a494bf73fc1d9bc26","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Retrospective for session 12 appended to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-27.md`.\n\nKey findings:\n\n- **Zero productive work.** Session 12 is the 4th consecutive session (9-12) that only fixed state corruption caused by ralph's reconciliation code.\n- **$2.58 spent, 11 API calls.** Cheapest of the 4 fix sessions. Cumulative waste from this bug today: ~$36.\n- **The state reconciliation bug (story 11-3) has been flagged in 7 consecutive retros without being fixed.** It resets `done` stories to `review` by ignoring git history and proof documents.\n- **Two CRITICAL action items:** (1) Guard `done` as an immutable terminal state in reconciliation code. (2) Add ralph session termination when sprint is 100% complete. Both are likely <30 minutes of work each and would eliminate the entire waste category.\n- **Cumulative project cost: $630.26** for 74 stories across 16 epics. The productive cost per story (~$3.36) is reasonable; the waste is concentrated in post-sprint state corruption loops."}],"totalDurationMs":116890,"totalTokens":44801,"totalToolUseCount":12,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3410,"cache_read_input_tokens":41091,"output_tokens":299,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"s